[[ ~ First Map on CS:S ~ ]]

This is a sniper training map I made. I made this because i always got shot in my head and wanted a way of training myself. This was great help for me and could be great help for you if your not that great at sniping. This is not proly made.. I just took all the skills of making maps I know and put it to this map. The big hills are not that good because i don't know how to make them good. Just hope you like this map.

~ Extra

~ [Put Money to $99999999 to buy sniper or steal from shelf]
~ [Shop Time: Put what you wish but if you run out of ammo, just put the shop time to 999]

Thank you and have Fun!

If you wish to know this easter egg, read more..



Easter Egg:

Not the best Easter egg but you can shoot the gun from above the shop if you wish not to buy the items.. This is not the best Easter egg, but I didn't really want to make one :P

A small fun map where each team starts out in their room.
Guns are not really used here, but pressing buttons and creating a pillar to be dropped on your enemy's base is.

User presses a button on his base, causes pillar to drop in specific place determined by button, pillar being dropped smashes anything in its way.

Be careful, and be fast!
Remember, what you do to their team they can do to you! 

Small map recommend maximum of 12 people. 6 on each team.


Watch your head,
Disturbed.

The scenerio of the map is there are 5 terrorists that have fortified them selves inside a run down building, and are holding 3 hostages. There are 20 counter terrorists making an assault.

The idea of the map is that 5 human players are on the T side, while 20 CT bots assault the 5 human players. While human players could play on both sides, it was intended for the use i stated above.

This is the first public version, the hostages do not move, and there are a few weird lights/ bugs.

The concept could not be simpler: the map is a large rectangle divided into two parts along its length by a transparent glass wall, and adopt a style desert (de_dust textures). In each of these parties, there is a base, which lies on a bucket, then the opposite, at the bottom of the map, a cage similar to a cage of football. The terrorists appear on one side, nearly a bucket, while the anti-terrorist appears on the other, next to another bucket. Both teams can not shoot because a glass wall separates them. 10 seconds after respawn, the glass surrounding the bucket down on the wooden base is broken, and each team must bring the bucket in cages at the bottom of the map, as soon as possible. The first team to successfully place the bucket in cages blew the other team, and a new round begins.
